Style guide
* Always declare document type (<!DOCTYPE html>)
* Use lowercase element names
* Always close all tags
* Always put attribute values in quotes
* Always specify alt, width and height for images
* Avoid spacing after equal signs (makes it easier to read)
* Indent appropriately
* Never skip the title element
* Always use <html>, <body>, <head> tags
* Always include the language attribute (<html> lang=“en-us”>)
* Always use meta tag
